Date: Sun, 1 Aug 2010 20:47:00 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] configure: fix __GMP_BITS_PER_MP_LIMB check for newer GMP

The CLFS book provided this patch to help find newer versions of GMP
properly.
---
 configure |    2 +-
 1 files changed, 1 insertions(+), 1 deletions(-)

diff --git a/configure b/configure
index 4f3dfc2..217c8ce 100755
--- a/configure
+++ b/configure
@@ -16473,7 +16473,7 @@ main() {
       || GMP_LIMB_BITS != mp_bits_per_limb) {
     std::cerr
       << "GMP header (gmp.h) and library (ligmp.*) bits-per-limb mismatch:\n"
-      << "header gives " << __GMP_BITS_PER_MP_LIMB << ";\n"
+      << "header gives " << GMP_LIMB_BITS << ";\n"
       << "library gives " << mp_bits_per_limb << ".\n"
       << "This probably means you are on a bi-arch system and\n"
       << "you are compiling with the wrong header or linking with\n"
